<p><strong>The Clocks by Agatha Christie: A Guide to the Novel</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. Who is the main character in "The Clocks"?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Hercule Poirot</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. What is the central mystery in the novel?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A series of seemingly random household objects are found at the scene of a murder, all set to different times.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>3. Who are the suspects in the case?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The residents of the boarding house where the murder takes place, including Sheila Webb, Colin Lamb, and Miss Williams.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>4. How does Poirot solve the mystery?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>By connecting the times on the objects to the events of a past crime and uncovering a conspiracy involving hidden relationships and mistaken identities.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>5. What is the significance of the title "The Clocks"?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The clocks represent the different viewpoints and timelines that Poirot must navigate to piece together the truth. They also symbolize the importance of time and its role in the unraveling of the mystery.</li>
</ul>
